From fd7dd07425a12656beb57e6e9af92e00459aee76 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Yi Ding <yi.s.ding@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 06:21:45 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 51/65] media: rockchip: rga: fix default-core sentinel check

Plain-language impact:
Fallback IOMMU scheduler selection tests whether an index has been chosen.

Kernel details:
another_index is initialized to -1. Compare another_index < 0 instead of comparing an index to the RGA_NONE_CORE bitmask constant.

Source: split from patches/cleanup-draft after docs/11-bsp-audit.md verification.
Signed-off-by: Yi Ding <yi.s.ding@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/video/rockchip/rga3/rga_iommu.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/video/rockchip/rga3/rga_iommu.c b/drivers/video/rockchip/rga3/rga_iommu.c
index a985695b5630..1cec62e8bb91 100644
--- a/drivers/video/rockchip/rga3/rga_iommu.c
+++ b/drivers/video/rockchip/rga3/rga_iommu.c
@@ -337,7 +337,7 @@ int rga_iommu_bind(void)
 
 			break;
 		default:
-			if (another_index != RGA_NONE_CORE)
+			if (another_index < 0)
 				another_index = i;
 
 			break;
-- 
2.53.0

